      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/12/1886. ¶  ¶ I was very pleased, esteemed Mr Holtze, to obtain the flowers of the bamboo, and as a result I succeeded in determining that it is a true  ¶ Bambusa ¶ , although it remains desirable ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">86.12.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, Public Library, Museum &amp; Art Gallery, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">12/12/86</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sehr erfreulich war es mir, geehrter Herr Holtze, die Blüthen des Bambus zu erlangen; — u gelang es mir, darnach festzustellen, dass es eine echte <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name> ist, obwohl es wünschenswerth bleibt, die Körner </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">gereift</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> zu erlangen, um diese generische Stellung zu bestätigen.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es sind jetzt nahe 200 <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>ceen aus den Tropenländern bekannt, u. diese sind in eine Anzahl verschiedener Genera vertheilt, so dass der reife Same auch nöthig ist, um das genaue Genus anzugeben. Da Sie die Blüthen im Nov. fanden, sollte der Same wohl im Jan. oder Februar reif sein. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nun möchte ich Sie bitten, mir eine </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">recht genaue</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> u vollständige Mittheilung über die Höhe, den Wuchs, den Standort, die </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">geographische Verbreitung</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> dieser <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name> zu machen; — mir auch freundlichst mitzutheilen, ob Sie mit Mr Fölsche darin übereinstimmen, dass </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">dort</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> noch eine zweite (kleinere?) Art vorkommt. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Wir kennen aus ganz Australien nur ausser Ihrer Art noch eine andere <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>cea in sehr beschränkter Verbreitung am Daintree u einigen anderen Flüssen im Nordöstl. Queensland, aber das wird wohl nicht eine echte <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name> sein; so ist die Ermittlung der 2 oder 3 austral Arten von besonders </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hohem Interesse</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">!</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich habe Trichosanthes Holtzei in den Druck gesandt; Sie erinnern wohl die <name key="Cucurbitacea">Cucurbitacea</name> mit weissen </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">gefranzten</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Blumen; um die Beschreibung zu vollenden hätte ich gern reife Früchte dieser schönen Schlingpflanze. </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sie ehrend und Ihnen ein frohes Neujahr wünschend</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Ich würde rathen, eine starke Wurzel mit Schösslingen des <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name> zur Ausstellung nach Adelaide zu senden; möchte auch gern selbst eine Wurzel haben.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Die geschickten Blüthen waren eigentlich für genaue Untersuchung noch zu jung.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/12/1886.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was very pleased, esteemed Mr Holtze, to obtain the flowers of the bamboo, and as a result I succeeded in determining that it is a true <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>
               </seg>, although it remains desirable to acquire <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ripened</hi>
               </seg> seeds to confirm this generic position.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Nearly 200 <name key="Bambusaceae">Bambusaceae</name> are now known from tropical countries, and these are divided into a number of different genera, so that the ripe seed is also necessary, to specify the correct genus. As you found the flowers in November, the seed ought to be ripe in January or February.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I now want to ask you to provide me with a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">very exact</hi>
               </seg> and complete notice on the height, the growth habit, the locality, and the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">geographical distribution</hi>
               </seg> of this <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>
               </seg>. Please be so kind to tell me also, whether you agree with Mr Foelsche, that a second (smaller?) species occurs <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">there</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Apart from your species we know only one other <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>cea from the whole of Australia with a very limited distribution at the Daintree and a few other rivers in north-eastern Queensland, but that will probably not be a true <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>
               </seg>; so the ascertaining of the 2 or 3 Australian species is of particularly <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">great interest</hi>
               </seg>!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have sent <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Trichosanthes%20holtzei">Trichosanthes holtzei</name>
               </seg> to the printers;<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B86.12.01.</p>
               </note> you probably recall the <name key="Cucurbitacea">Cucurbitacea</name> with the white, <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fringed</hi>
               </seg> flowers. To complete the description, I would like to have ripe fruit of this lovely climbing plant.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to M. Holtze, 24 January 1885, and M to M. Holtze, 3 December 1886 (in this edition as 86-12-03b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Conveying you my respects and wishing you a happy New Year</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I would advise that you send a strong root with shoots of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>
               </seg> to the Exhibition in Adelaide;<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Jubilee International Exhibition, Adelaide, 1887; the list of Holtze’s exhibits does not include any bamboo (Scott (1887), pp. 253-4).</p>
               </note> I would also like to have a root myself.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The flowers you sent were really still too young for an accurate examination.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bambusa">Bambusa</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bambusaceae">Bambusaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cucurbitacea">Cucurbitacea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Trichosanthes%20holtzei">Trichosanthes holtzei</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
